#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/lena/skills/marketing-and-growth/content-strategy/references/headless-cms.md savings=4%
M|Head|tx|Reference for choosing, modeling, and implementing a headless CMS for mk cn.
M|When|tx|Use this when selecting a CMS for a new project, designing cn md for mk sites, setting up editorial workflows, or connecting CMS cn to programmatic pages.
M|When|tx|---
M|Head|tx|A headless CMS separates cn management from presentation. cn is stored in a structured backend and delivered via ap to any frontend.
M|When|it|Multiple frontends consume the same cn (web, mobile, em)
M|When|it|Developers want full control over the frontend stack
M|When|it|cn needs to be reused across channels
M|When|it|You're building w/ a modern framework (nx.js, Remix, Astro)
M|When|it|mk needs structured, reusable cn blocks
M|When|it|Small team w/ no dedicated developers
M|When|it|Simple blog or brochure site
M|When|it|WYSIWYG editing is a hard requirement
M|When|it|Budget is tight and WordPress/Webflow does the job
M|Deci|tx|\| Factor \| Headless \| Traditional \|
M|Deci|tx|\|--------\|----------\|-------------\|
M|Deci|tx|\| Multi-channel delivery \| Yes \| Limited \|
M|Deci|tx|\| Developer control \| Full \| Constrained \|
M|Deci|tx|\| Non-tc editing \| Requires setup \| Built-in \|
M|Deci|tx|\| Time to launch \| Longer \| Faster \|
M|Deci|tx|\| cn reuse \| Native \| Manual \|
M|Deci|tx|\| Hosting flexibility \| Any frontend \| Platform-dependent \|
M|Deci|tx|---
M|Core|tx|1. **Think in tp, not pages.** A "Landing Page" is a cn tp w/ fields — not an HTML file. This lets you reuse cp across pages.
M|Core|tx|2. **Separate cn from presentation.** Store the hl text, not the styled hl. Presentation belongs in the frontend.
M|Core|tx|3. **ds for reuse.** If testimonials appear on 5 pages, cr a Testimonial tp and reference it — don't duplicate.
M|Core|tx|4. **Keep md flat.** Deeply nested structures are hard to query and maintain. Prefer references over nesting.
M|Comm|tx|\| tp \| Key Fields \| Notes \|
M|Comm|tx|\|------\|-----------\|-------\|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Landing Page** \| title, slug, hero, sections[], seo \| Modular sections for flexibility \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Blog Post** \| title, slug, body, author, category, tags, publishedAt, seo \| Rich text or Portable Text body \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Case Study** \| title, cs, challenge, solution, results, metrics[], logo \| Link to related pd/features \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Testimonial** \| quote, author, role, company, avatar, rating \| Reference from landing pages \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **FAQ** \| question, answer, category \| Group by category for programmatic pages \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Author** \| name, bio, avatar, sl links \| Reference from blog posts \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **CTA Block** \| heading, body, buttonText, buttonUrl, variant \| Reusable across pages \|
M|SEO |Ever|
M|SEO |it|`metaTitle` — 50-60 characters
M|SEO |it|`metaDescription` — 150-160 characters
M|SEO |it|`ogImage` — 1200x630px sl preview
M|SEO |it|`slug` — URL path segment
M|SEO |it|`canonicalUrl` — optional override
M|SEO |it|`noIndex` — boolean for excluding from search
M|SEO |it|`structuredData` — optional JSON-LD override
M|SEO |tx|---
M|Draf|tx|1. **Draft** — Author creates or edits cn
M|Draf|tx|2. **rv** — Editor reviews for accuracy, br voice, SEO
M|Draf|tx|3. **ap** — Stakeholder signs off
M|Draf|tx|4. **Schedule** — Set publish date/time
M|Draf|tx|5. **Publish** — cn goes live via ap
M|Prev|All |
M|Prev|- **|Real-time preview w/ `useLiveQuery` or Presentation tool
M|Prev|- **|Preview ap (`preview.contentful.com`) w/ separate access tk
M|Prev|- **|Draft & Publish sy w/ `status=draft` query parameter (v5; replaces v4's `publicationState`)
M|Prev|tx|Set up a preview rt in your frontend (e.g., `/ap/preview`) that authenticates and renders draft cn.
M|Role|tx|\| Role \| Can cr \| Can Edit \| Can Publish \| Can dl \|
M|Role||---|----------:\|:--------:\|:-----------:\|:----------:\|
M|Role|tx|\| Author \| Yes \| Own \| No \| Own drafts \|
M|Role|tx|\| Editor \| Yes \| All \| Yes \| Drafts \|
M|Role|tx|\| Admin \| Yes \| All \| Yes \| All \|
M|Role|tx|Exact permission md vary by platform. Sanity uses role-based access. Contentful has space-level roles. Strapi has granular RBAC.
M|Role|tx|---
M|Plat|tx|\| Feature \| Sanity \| Contentful \| Strapi \|
M|Plat|tx|\|---------\|--------\|------------\|--------\|
M|Plat|tx|\| Hosting \| Cloud (managed) \| Cloud (managed) \| Self-hosted or Cloud \|
M|Plat|tx|\| Query Language \| GROQ \| REST / GraphQL \| REST / GraphQL \|
M|Plat|tx|\| Free Tier \| Generous \| Limited \| Open source (free) \|
M|Plat|tx|\| Real-time Collab \| Yes (built-in) \| Limited \| No \|
M|Plat|tx|\| Best For \| Developer flexibility \| Enterprise multi-locale \| Budget / self-hosted \|
M|Plat|tx|\| cn Modeling \| sc-as-code \| Web UI \| Web UI or code \|
M|Plat|tx|\| Media Handling \| Built-in DAM \| Built-in \| Plugin-based \|
M|Sani|**St|GROQ query language is powerful and flexible. sc defined in code (version-controlled). Real-time collaborative editing. Portable Text for rich cn. Generous free tier.
M|Sani|**Co|Steeper learning curve for non-developers. Studio customization requires rc knowledge. Vendor lock-in on GROQ queries.
M|Sani|**Ma|Best when developers and marketers collaborate closely. Strong for cn-heavy sites w/ complex md.
M|Cont|**St|Mature enterprise platform. Excellent multi-locale support. Strong ecosystem of integrations. Composable cn w/ Studio. Well-documented APIs.
M|Cont|**Co|Pricing scales w/ cn tp and locales. Two separate APIs (Delivery and Management). Rate limits can be tight on lower plans.
M|Cont|**Ma|Best for enterprises w/ multi-mk cn needs. Good when you need established vendor reliability.
M|Stra|**St|Open source, self-hosted option. Full control over data. No per-seat pricing. Customizable admin panel. Plugin ecosystem. REST by default, GraphQL via plugin.
M|Stra|**Co|Self-hosting means you handle infrastructure. Smaller ecosystem than Sanity/Contentful. V5 migration can be sig from V4.
M|Stra|**Ma|Best for teams w/ DevOps capability who want full control and no vendor lock-in. Good for budget-conscious projects.
M|Othe|it|**Hygraph** — GraphQL-native, strong for federation and multi-source cn
M|Othe|it|**Keystatic** — Git-based, good for developer-cn hybrid workflows
M|Othe|it|**Payload** — ts-first, self-hosted, code-configured like Sanity
M|Othe|it|**Builder.io** — Visual editor w/ headless backend, good for non-tc marketers
M|Othe|it|**Prismic** — Slice-based cn modeling, strong nx.js integration
M|Othe|tx|---
M|Prog|tx|Use CMS as the data source for programmatic pages. Store structured data (FAQs, comparisons, city pages) as cn tp and gn pages from queries. See **programmatic-seo** skill.
M|Copy|tx|CMS cn md enforce consistent structure. Define fields that match your cp frameworks (hl, subheadline, sl proof, CTA). See **copywriting** skill.
M|Site|tx|URL structure, navigation hierarchy, and internal linking all depend on how cn is organized in the CMS. Plan your cn md and site architecture together. See **site-architecture** skill.
M|Emai|tx|Pull CMS cn into em templates for consistent messaging across web and em. Case studies, testimonials, and blog posts can feed em nurture sequences. See **em-sequence** skill.
M|Emai|tx|---
M|Impl|it|[ ] Define cn tp based on page tp and reusable blocks
M|Impl|it|[ ] Add SEO fields to every page-level cn tp
M|Impl|it|[ ] Set up preview/draft mode in your frontend
M|Impl|it|[ ] Configure roles and permissions for your team
M|Impl|it|[ ] cr sample cn for each tp before building frontend
M|Impl|it|[ ] Set up webhook notifications for cn changes (rebuild triggers)
M|Impl|it|[ ] Document cn guidelines for editors (field descriptions, character limits)
M|Impl|it|[ ] tst cn delivery perf (CDN, caching, ISR)
M|Impl|it|[ ] Plan migration st if moving from existing CMS
M|Impl|tx|---
M|Rele|it|[Sanity](../../../tools/integrations/sanity.md) — GROQ queries, mutations, CLI
M|Rele|it|[Contentful](../../../tools/integrations/contentful.md) — Delivery/Management APIs, publishing
M|Rele|it|[Strapi](../../../tools/integrations/strapi.md) — REST CRUD, filters, document ap